    "abstract": "<jats:title>Abstract</jats:title>\n                <jats:p>The SARS-CoV-2 pandemic continues to be driven by viral variants. Most research has focused on structural proteins and on site-specific mutations. Here, we describe recombination events involving genomic terminal sequences in SARS-CoV-2 and related viruses leading to structural rearrangements in terminal and coding regions and discuss their potential contributions to viral variation, replication, pathogenicity, and immune evasion.</jats:p>",
